<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-45-1151 </DOCNO><TEXT>The energy differences between atoms and between molecules that containonly one non-common atom can be expressed with a high degree of accuracyin terms of the electrostatic potentials at the non-common nucleus. Theenergy is given as a sum of terms, rather than a difference. In manyinstances, electrostatic potentials obtained from Hartee-Fock wave functionsgive energy differences more accurate than the Hartee-Fock delta E.</TEXT></DOC>